{"questionId":"9067496","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Copper forms two chlorides, copper(I) chloride and copper(II) chloride.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Two electrolysis cells were assembled using graphite electrodes and connected in series as shown.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0e2b920773da8385077e300e7d4c4df46d8aad7a.png\"></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State how current is conducted through the wires and through the electrolyte.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Wires:&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Electrolyte:</span></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Wires</em>:<br>«delocalized» electrons «flow» ✔<br></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Electrolyte</em>:<br>«mobile» ions «flow» ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067496","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.c(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State how current is conducted through the wires and through the electrolyte. Wires: Electrolyte:","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 9: Redox processes","9.2 Electrochemical cells","Core","Topic 9: Redox processes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}